---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Welcome Home
hero_title: "Fast. Simple. Static."
hero_subtitle: "This site is powered by Eleventy and managed via Git."
featured_image: "/assets/uploads/hero.jpg"
---

<section class="hero">
  <h1>{{ hero_title }}</h1>
  <p>{{ hero_subtitle }}</p>
  <a href="/contact" class="btn">Get Started</a>
</section>

<section class="features">
  <h2>Why this setup?</h2>
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Eleventy Speed</h3>
      <p>Zero client-side JS by default. Your users get content instantly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>GitCMS Workflow</h3>
      <p>Edit content in a UI; it commits directly to your repository.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="latest-posts">
  <h2>Latest Updates</h2>
  <ul>
    {%- for post in collections.post | reverse | limit(3) -%}
      <li>
        <a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a> 
        <span>â€” {{ post.date | postDate }}</span>
      </li>
    {%- else -%}
      <li>No posts found yet. Start writing in the CMS!</li>
    {%- endfor -%}
  </ul>
</section>